  <exercise label="ex_css_3">
    <statement>
      <p>Suppose you are working on a recipe website.  Recipes have a title, a list of ingredients, and an instructions section.  Make a webpage that shows the recipe for grilled cheese sandwiches with bacon and tomato.   The ingredients should be displayed as an unordered list, with no bullets.  meat ingredients should have a light red background color, vegetables should have a light green background, and dairy products should have a light yellow.  The title should be in a sans serif font of your choice, and the instructions should have a heading <q>Instructions</q> and the font for the instructions should be italic.</p>
    </statement>
    <listing>
    <program xml:id="ex_css_3_editor" interactive="activecode" language="html" label="program-activecode-css-e3" include-source="yes">
      <prefix>


</prefix>
      <input>


        </input>
      <tests>


</tests>
    </program>
  </listing>
  </exercise>
